# Installation

## Requirements

- Python {{ min_python_version }} or higher
- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) (recommended) or pip
{% if publish_to_pypi %}
## Install from PyPI

/// tab | uv
```bash
uv add {{ project_name }}
```
///

/// tab | pip
```bash
pip install {{ project_name }}
```
///
{% endif %}
{%- if repository_provider == 'github' %}
## Install from Source

You can install directly from GitHub:

/// tab | uv
```bash
uv add git+{{ repository }}
```
///

/// tab | pip
```bash
pip install git+{{ repository }}
```
///

Or clone the repository:

```bash
git clone {{ repository }}
cd {{ project_name }}
```
{% endif %}

## Install for Development

Clone the repository and set up the development environment:

/// tab | make
```bash
make setup-dev
```
///

/// tab | mise
```bash
mise run setup:dev
```
///

This will install all dependencies (including dev dependencies) and set up pre-commit hooks.

!!! note
    This project requires both [`mise`](https://mise.jdx.dev/) and [`uv`](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) to be installed.
    `make` tasks proxy through `mise run`, which in turn invokes `uv` and other tools.
{% if with_typer_cli %}
## CLI Installation

To use the CLI without activating the virtual environment every time:

/// tab | make
```bash
make setup-cli
```
///

/// tab | mise
```bash
mise run setup:cli
```
///

!!! note
    `setup:cli` installs the CLI with `uv tool install`. It is available **everywhere** only
    when `uv` is installed globally (on your `PATH`) — not just provided through `mise`. If
    `uv` is only available via `mise`, the CLI still runs without activating the virtualenv,
    but only from within the project directory.

After installation, you can run the CLI with:

```bash
{{ cli_name }} --help
```
